Sentencas: Mn0.9Y0.1CO2O4 spinel coatings are developed for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) alloy interconnects by a novel powder reduction technique.
Titulo: Development of the spinel powder reduction technique for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect coating

Sentencas: Material properties, electrical performance and long-term stability of the coatings are explored.
Titulo: Development of the spinel powder reduction technique for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect coating

Sentencas: The coating is about 9 gm in thickness and adheres well to the alloy substrate without any cracking or delamination.
Titulo: Development of the spinel powder reduction technique for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect coating

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) remains almost unchanged and is less than 3 m Omega cm(2) even though the coated alloy undergoes oxidation at 800 degrees C for 1017 h and ten thermal cycles from 800 degrees C to room temperature.
Titulo: Development of the spinel powder reduction technique for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect coating

Sentencas: The coated alloy presents excellent electrical performance and long-term stability.
Titulo: Development of the spinel powder reduction technique for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect coating

Sentencas: It exhibits a promising prospect for the practical application of SOFC alloy interconnect.
Titulo: Development of the spinel powder reduction technique for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect coating
